2- killing with grenades;
3- killing of people inside the government (based on ethnic or/and a leader struggling for his life?);
4- no clear signal that it will be a sufficient and rapid international intervention;
5- presence of para military groups;
6- citizens are confused if the killings are coming from the government.
Some observers talked about Burundi like a civil war...like Roméo Dallaire wrote in his book.
What i am reading now from the book and the news is confuse me. Hope that i am wrong.

